RACE.FOOTNOTES: MUSIC TO MY EARS unhurried early, swept up wide past quarter pole, cleared stretch, held on to the wire gamely. DARK HEDGES inside run to turn, blocked past quarter pole, got clear for place spot in a game effort. POWELL bobbled bit after start, lagged back to the turn, ran on in the stretch to settle for show. SAMURAI SAINT pinched back start, raced back to turn, rallied on to improve. KITTENS ADAIR trailed to the quarter pole, kept on in the stretch, improved. ALFIE SOLOMONS inside to duel, gave way from quarter pole and faded in the stretch run. UNCLE EARL between horses with pace to quarter pole, bore out, faded. PRINCE ACT bore in start, with pack to the turn, gave way readily stretch.
